  "last_gate": {
    "recommendation": "PROCEED",
    "rationale": "Both unresolved flags are executor-level implementation details, not planning gaps. FLAG-001 (keyboard accessibility) is a one-line addition of KeyboardSensor alongside PointerSensor in the nested DndContext \u2014 the plan's architecture already supports it. FLAG-003 (no automated tests) is a valid concern but the reorder logic is pure and testable; the executor can add a test file during Step 2 or Step 6 without any plan restructuring. The plan itself is well-phased (bugs first, then drag), correctly identifies the root causes, respects the visual-before-audio invariant, and isolates track DnD from clip DnD via nested DndContext. No debt subsystem overlaps or recurring critiques to worry about.",
    "signals_assessment": "Iteration 1, weighted score 3.5, no prior trajectory. Two significant flags remain but both are additive implementation details (add a sensor, add a test file) rather than architectural corrections. No plan delta to evaluate, no recurring critiques, no scope creep. Preflight is fully clean. The score reflects the open flags but the plan's structure is stable and doesn't need revision to address them.",
    "warnings": [
      "Executor should add KeyboardSensor to the nested DndContext (Step 7) to preserve keyboard reorder accessibility \u2014 don't ship pointer-only.",
      "Executor should add at least one vitest file covering same-kind boundary enforcement in handleReorderTrack/handleMoveTrack, following the existing pattern in serialize.test.ts."
    ],
    "settled_decisions": [
      {
        "id": "DECISION-001",
        "decision": "Use a nested DndContext for track reordering rather than the app-level DndContext.",
        "rationale": "Isolates track drag events from clip/shot DnD. The plan correctly identified this as the safer approach given the existing app-level DnD wiring."
      },
      {
        "id": "DECISION-002",
        "decision": "Maintain the visual-before-audio track ordering invariant; reordering is within-kind-group only.",
        "rationale": "Consistent with sortTracksByKind enforcement on load. Cross-kind reordering would require schema and UX changes beyond this scope."
      },
      {
        "id": "DECISION-003",
        "decision": "Phase the work: fix reorder bugs first (Steps 1-3), then layer drag-to-reorder (Steps 4-8).",
        "rationale": "Bug fixes are independently valuable and validate the reorder logic before building the drag UX on top of it."
      }
    ],
